FBIS4-30681 "dreas125_n_94010" FBIS-EAS-94-125 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 Vietnam 40 Billion Dong Allocated for Drug Programs 40 Billion Dong Allocated for Drug Programs BK2706031494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 0500 GMT 24 Jun 94 BK2706031494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] According to an announcement issued by the Committee for Nationalities and Mountainous Regions, in 1994, the state budget allocates more than 40 billion dong for national programs to prevent and fight drug addiction. This funding reserves 25 billion dong for expenses to increase production and replace poppy trees in all northern provinces and 10 billion dong for drug rehabilitation and social welfare issues relating to drug addiction in all localities.
